PasswordProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Derived subclasses usually implement a password prompt, although they may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also choose to provide a password from elsewhere. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be filled in and then ","type":"text"},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be called. Alternatively the user may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"abort this password request, which will usually abort the TLS connection."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation can either be a synchronous (eg: modal dialog) or an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asynchronous one (eg: modeless dialog). This function will take care of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling which ever one correctly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the interaction is cancelled by the cancellation object, or by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"user then "},{"code":"failed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned with an error that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contains a "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" error code. Certain implementations may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not support immediate cancellation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSInteractionRef/TLSInteractionProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","title":"TLSInteractionProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsinteractionref\/tlsinteractionprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO